<br>
What I try hardest to do is to work with other guilds about our size these days. Guild alliances to work together on raids are great. They have the effect of also getting folks to know each other, so that when an LFG is up, you don't have the same sense of a pickup group if it's a guild you've raided with.<br>
<br>
About the work-load. Don't expect anyone to be able to do any one job forever. Ask them to do it for three months, then find someone else if they want to turn that over. If you delegate with a fixed time, people don't mind as much putting in the time.<br>
<br>
Some GLs are benign dictators, a model that has a lot going for it if the &quot;benign&quot; really is there. In our guild, we do run almost everything past membership for final review and comment. And we're serious about it, it isn't just a formality to keep the rank and file thinking that they are participating. Slows down getting things done, but worth it. We also now have votes of confidence on our slate of officers about every six months. We don't believe in officers for life. <br>
<br>
More important than anything, your guild's reputation is worth everything. No camp, no disagreement, no loot, nothing is worth tarnishing your guild's rep. I'm not saying that people should roll over to folks who bully their way into their camp. But there's almost always is a way to come to a meeting of the minds. We ask our members to watch their manners in ooc, shout, even on other boards. At least most of the time. We may be the very last guild to ever see the endgame once everyone else is tired of EQ or has gone on to EQ2, but we'll get there with our values intact. That matters to us a lot. <p> <font face="Arial"><div align="center"><font color="Red"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=359805" target="_blank">Epix</a></a><br>64 Sorcerer<br>Guild Leader, Grey Council on Xev<br></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm12.showPrevMessage?topicID=3.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm12.showNextMessage?topicID=3.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm12.emailToFriend?topicID=3.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm12.threadControl?topicID=3.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm12.subsc